 To achieve its objectives, development cooperation needs private-sector involvement. The BMZ initiates development partnerships with the private sector (developpp.de). These partnerships address mutual interests and leverage the particular strengths of each partner. GIZ offers an extensive range of services for interested companies on tools and processes for cooperation with the private sector. <BR>

##PageID 3447
TEXT_content
 Reforms of social services are driven by the aim to align these services with the needs and expectations of their users. Systemic quality improvement is an instrument developed by GIZ, which is to promote this process. The SQI approach makes it possible to connect the development both of an entire system and of individual organisational units within it.

##PageID 3448
TEXT_content
 Twinning means establishing partnerships of public administrations between member states of the European Union and countries that are either current or potential EU accession candidates. The EU finances twinning projects and sectoral authorities in many EU states apply to implement these projects. Since 2000, GIZ has been involved in the successful implementation of some 200 twinning projects. <BR>

##PageID 3450
TEXT_content
 <p>The European Commission awards grants via its thematic and regional programmes. We have long-standing experience in international cooperation and can support German federal ministries and other public institutions in this context. This includes specific knowledge related to applying for EU grants and comprehensive expertise in implementing and evaluating projects.</p>

##PageID 3451
TEXT_content
 <p>As a tool for training and networking people that are spread far and wide, e-Learning can play a key role in achieving your project objectives. We advise our clients and partners on the development and implementation of e-Learning, e-Coaching and e-Collaboration.</p>

##PageID 3452
TEXT_content
 Which social effects are produced by political reforms and development measures? GIZ together with other implementing organisations and donors has developed approaches that allow this question to be answered. The results of these analyses provide tangible information on the impacts that people, and poor people especially, can expect.

##PageID 3453
TEXT_content
 Networks have become key facilitators in successful international cooperation. They promote exchanges and mutual learning amongst their members with regard to cross-sectoral issues, regional developments and methodological procedure. They are good for fostering decision-making and the achievement of objectives. We support our clients in all network management processes. <BR>

##PageID 3455
TEXT_content
 Knowledge management supports organisations and networks in achieving their goals through an effective an efficient exchange of high-quality knowledge. We support you in finding weaknesses in your current knowledge management, developing new strategies, choose appropriate instruments and if necessary training and coaching your staff.

##PageID 3456
TEXT_content
 Stakeholder-dialogues bring together governmental and non-governmental stakeholders. They aim at negotiating interests, formulating a common goal and then taking action. This helps taking viable decisions. We support this process in order to get stakeholder-dialogues going and keeping them on track. <BR>

##PageID 3457
TEXT_content
 <p>Successful organisations maintain links with former associates and work with them to achieve their goals. Associates become partners that support you in all areas of your work: learning, marketing, knowledge management, training and finance. They also help establish new contacts. </p>
        <p>We can turn your alumni into an international network of disseminators, considerably increasing the impact of your work.</p>

##PageID 3458
TEXT_content
 <p>Effective and efficient procurement systems are indispensable for a properly functioning state. We support our partners in two distinct ways: Firstly we help our partners to put in place functioning structures and institutions to handle public procurement. Secondly GIZ offers its services as procurement agent or fund manager. </p>

##PageID 3459
TEXT_content
 A project is only considered successful if the planned results - that is the changes that can be causally and plausibly attributed to the project - can be substantiated. The results-based monitoring system helps our partners' projects and programmes to align themselves with managing for development results. GIZ offers advisory and training packages on applying the system.

##PageID 3460
TEXT_content
 <p>Funds are a way to provide financing for international activities in selected sectors quickly and efficiently. We provide professional support to both clients and partners in setting up and managing funds.</p>

##PageID 3461
