##PageID 5223
TEXT_content
 <p>The introduction of Capacity WORKS changed the requirements GIZ places on its cooperation partners in the consultancy sector. These providers must now align their work with the Capacity WORKS management model. This means that when GIZ advertises positions for long-term experts, it expects these individuals to also possess expertise in Capacity WORKS.</p>
        <p>Since January 2012, the training courses previously conducted by the ‘Capacity WORKS multipliers’ are now being carried out by GIZ itself. These training activities for individual consultants and consulting companies are implemented by GIZ’s own Academy for International Cooperation (AIZ).</p>
        <p>Courses are held at GIZ’s training centres in Bad Honnef, Feldafing and Berlin. On request courses may also be held at other locations, e.g. on the premises of consulting companies.</p>

