 <p>In addition to the completed online application form, we will need <strong>a covering letter, your current CV and your last two school report cards</strong>. Please upload these documents using the system and submit them as attachments. You can, of course, also attach other references and certificates (internship references, etc.).</p>
        <p>A maximum of 10 MB can be uploaded per application. <br />
        <br />
        The following maximum file sizes apply to individual documents:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Covering letter and photo – 1MB each; CV and other documents – 2MB each </li>
        </ul>
        <p>The system accepts the following file types:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>CV, covering letter, other documents: doc, docx, pdf</li>
            <li>Photo: bmp, gif, jpg</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We cannot accept any applications submitted by post.</strong></p>

##PageID 7628
TEXT_content
 <p>The information contained in your application will automatically be transferred to a database that can only be accessed from within GIZ. When you submit your application form, you automatically consent to your data being stored electronically.</p>
        <p>Once the applications have been processed and preferred applicants shortlisted, we will decide which applicants will be invited to attend the selection day. These are generally held at the end of October.</p>
        <p>The vocational traineeships then start in August of the following year.</p>
        <p>Click on the link on the right of the page to view all our current vacancies.</p>

